spec_data.Name: kdesrc-build
spec_data.License: GPLv2+ and LGPLv3+ and BSD and GFDL
spec_data.Description:
kdesrc-build is a script to help users install KDE software from its Subversion
and Git source repositories. It used to be called kdesvn-build, the name was
changed to this more generic form in June 2010 when KDE started adopting
git-based source control.
spec_data.Signature: RSA/SHA256, Sat 25 Feb 2017 12:54:14 PM EST, Key ID f55e7430f5282ee4
spec_data.Summary: A tool to easily build KDE from its source repositories
